      <abstract>
        <p>A standard buffer-series assay for measuring steady-state enzyme activity from pH 4.0 to pH 8.0 in 0.5-unit increments.</p>
      </abstract>
    </article-meta>
  </front>
  <body>
    <sec sec-type="materials">
      <title>Materials</title>
      <p>Buffer panel; activity substrate; standardized enzyme aliquots.</p>
    </sec>
    <sec sec-type="procedure">
      <title>Procedure</title>
      <list list-type="order">
        <list-item><label>1.</label><p>Prepare buffer panel spanning pH 4.0–8.0 in 0.5-unit steps.</p></list-item>
        <list-item><label>2.</label><p>Equilibrate enzyme aliquots at room temperature for 5 min.</p></list-item>
        <list-item><label>3.</label><p>Initiate assay with substrate; record activity at each pH (n=3 per condition).</p></list-item>
        <list-item><label>4.</label><p>Fit pH–activity curve and extract midpoint.</p></list-item>
      </list>
    </sec>
  </body>
